            <fr:title text="\rightarrow  preserves the property"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rightarrow ]]></fr:tex> preserves the property</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Again, I'll only look at one binary connective, since they all follow the same pattern of reasoning; this time I'll pick <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rightarrow ]]></fr:tex> for the sake of variety.
Here are the strong Kleene and Dunn-Belnap tables for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rightarrow ]]></fr:tex>:</html:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
